Java, March 1942: Only one available airplane and 5 pilots to choose from. Who will be the lucky one to go on mission against the Japs. All of them want to go but maybe someone have special reasons to go. The ones left behind reminisce over their encounters with the pilot who got to go.

Pilot#5, Writer David Hertz; directed by George Sidney and released by MGM.

Starring:

Franchot Tone - George Braynor Collins
Marsha Hunt  - Freddie Andrews
Gene Kelly - Vito S. Alessandro
Van Johnson - Everett Arnold
Alan Baxter - Winston Davis
Howard Freeman - Governor Hank Durban
